DTSTAMP:20260505T023751Z
UID:17ff1ac6-7ddb-480e-a0f8-b98dc21109aa
DTSTART:20260815T130000
DTEND:20260816T210000
DESCRIPTION:Dive into the world of Mid Century Modern design with our Funky
  Footstool Workshop. In this two-day course\, you'll learn the foundationa
 l skills of woodworking and upholstery by constructing a replica of the Mi
 d Century Modern footstool designed by Victor Wilkins.
SUMMARY:Mid Century Funky Footstool
URL;VALUE=URI:https://ce.sbwi.edu/s/courseoffering/0P0Hu000000TbwTKAS
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260505T023751Z
UID:5599f2f1-6f26-488e-80bb-63f2cba659a5
DTSTART:20260817T120000
DTEND:20260821T210000
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to completely design and build two stools in this fiv
 e-day class. Learn how to blend artistic form and functionality. This clas
 s was inspired by the innovative designs of Wharton Esherick\, a pioneerin
 g figure in the American studio furniture movement.
SUMMARY:Design & Build Esherick-Inspired Stools
URL;VALUE=URI:https://ce.sbwi.edu/s/courseoffering/0P0Hu000000TbwUKAS
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260505T023751Z
UID:7a614224-2307-4265-85ee-834eee356059
DTSTART:20260817T120000
DTEND:20260822T210000
DESCRIPTION:Your woodworking journey starts here\, with this 6-day intensiv
 e class.  Intro to Woodworking is designed for beginners interested the fu
 ndamentals of woodworking\, focusing on machine techniques.  No prior expe
 rience is required. With a maximum of 8 students\, you'll receive personal
 ized instruction in a fully equipped machine room. By the end of this clas
 s\, you will have the ability to tackle more woodworking projects on your 
 own.
SUMMARY:Intro to Woodworking
URL;VALUE=URI:https://ce.sbwi.edu/s/courseoffering/0P0Hu000000TbwhKAC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260505T023751Z
UID:cca18479-753e-4b7d-90e1-8f05c53312b5
DTSTART:20260824T120000
DTEND:20260828T210000
DESCRIPTION:This course will give students a foundational education in timb
 er framing while they work as a group to build and complete a timber frame
  pavilion. Students will gain an understanding of the materials\, tools an
 d safety standards used in the timber framing industry.
SUMMARY:Timber Framing
URL;VALUE=URI:https://ce.sbwi.edu/s/courseoffering/0P0Hu000000TbxpKAC
END:VEVENT
